üìò Day 1: React Basics (JSX, Components, Props, State)
üéØ Theory Learned

  
1. JSX
JSX allows writing HTML inside JavaScript.
Example:
const Welcome = () => <h1>Hello, Ashu!</h1>;

2. Functional Components
Small, reusable UI blocks.
Easy to test and maintain.

3. Props
Used to pass data from parent ‚Üí child components.
Example: <Card title="React" description="A UI library" />

4. State (useState)
Used to track UI changes inside a component.
Example: Toggling dark/light mode or showing/hiding sections.

üíº Use Cases
Industry Use Case:
Component-based dashboards (e.g., LinkedIn job cards, product listings).

Creative Use Case:
Resume sections (Education, Skills) as separate components that accept props and update live.


üìù Assignments Completed

1.Card Component with Props

function Card({ title, description }) {
  return (
    <div className="card">
      <h2>{title}</h2>
      <p>{description}</p>
    </div>
  );
}


2.Button Toggle with useState

import React, { useState } from "react";

export default function ToggleButton() {
  const [showMore, setShowMore] = useState(false);

  return (
    <div>
      <button onClick={() => setShowMore(!showMore)}>
        {showMore ? "Show Less" : "Show More"}
      </button>
      {showMore && <p>This is the extra content!</p>}
    </div>
  );
}


üöÄ Project Task ‚Äì Resume Builder (Day 1)
Goal

Create a Resume Builder with input fields (Name, Email, Skills).
Show live preview using props + state.




app.jsx

import React, { useState } from "react";
import Form from "./Form";
import Preview from "./Preview";

export default function App() {
  // State to store resume data
  const [resumeData, setResumeData] = useState({
    name: "",
    email: "",
    skills: ""
  });

  return (
    <div style={{ display: "flex", gap: "2rem", padding: "2rem" }}>
      {/* Input Form */}
      <Form resumeData={resumeData} setResumeData={setResumeData} />

      {/* Resume Preview */}
      <Preview
        name={resumeData.name}
        email={resumeData.email}
        skills={resumeData.skills}
      />
    </div>
  );
}


form.jsx

import React from "react";

export default function Form({ resumeData, setResumeData }) {
  const handleChange = (e) => {
    const { name, value } = e.target;
    setResumeData({ ...resumeData, [name]: value });
  };

  return (
    <div style={{ width: "300px" }}>
      <h2>Resume Form</h2>

      <label>
        Name: <br />
        <input
          type="text"
          name="name"
          value={resumeData.name}
          onChange={handleChange}
          placeholder="Enter your name"
        />
      </label>
      <br /><br />

      <label>
        Email: <br />
        <input
          type="email"
          name="email"
          value={resumeData.email}
          onChange={handleChange}
          placeholder="Enter your email"
        />
      </label>
      <br /><br />

      <label>
        Skills: <br />
        <input
          type="text"
          name="skills"
          value={resumeData.skills}
          onChange={handleChange}
          placeholder="e.g. React, JavaScript"
        />
      </label>
    </div>
  );
}


preview.jsx

import React from "react";

export default function Preview({ name, email, skills }) {
  return (
    <div style={{ border: "1px solid black", padding: "1rem", width: "300px" }}>
      <h2>Resume Preview</h2>
      <p><strong>Name:</strong> {name || "Enter your name"}</p>
      <p><strong>Email:</strong> {email || "Enter your email"}</p>
      <p><strong>Skills:</strong> {skills || "Enter your skills"}</p>
    </div>
  );
}
